step.context:
\text{To find }A^{-1}\text{ using elementary transformation,}\\ 
\text{how does one express A in terms of A and I,}\\ 
\text{where I is the } \textbf{identity matrix}\text{ ?}

step.reason:
\text{When using }\textbf{row } \text{transformation, I must be }\\ 
\text{the }\textbf{first}\text{ multiplier, whereas when using}\\
\textbf{column}\text{ transformation, it is the }\textbf{ second.}

\text{The above transformation(s) are correct. After}\\
\text{all transformations have been applied to the }\\
\text{first matrix on RHS, it becomes the inverse.}
